The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, May 06, 2004 				 ACC cements bottomline
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, May 5: Associated Cement Companies (ACC) has recorded a net profit of Rs 105.9 crore for the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2004 compared with Rs 58.7 crore in the year-ago period.																								Total income rose to Rs 1,040.07 crore (Rs 789.7 crore). In 2003-04, ACC posted a net profit of Rs 200.24 crore (Rs 103.89 crore) and a total income of Rs 3,435 crore (Rs 2,970.8 crore).																								During the quarter, cement sales rose 11 per cent to 4.04 million tonnes compared with 3.65 million tonnes in the year-ago period. ACC said the period witnessed better price realisation over the same period last year. 																								A rise in the prices of coal, gypsum and diesel was neutralised by a cut in cost due to improved operating efficiencies. 
